Cell.Text: Oh, it's you. I didn't expect to see you again.

Node.Caption: MQ201MalbornPostQuestTopic: Malborn, what are you doing here?

Cell.Text: Trying to stay ahead of the Thalmor assassins. I'm not a hero like you. I don't stand a chance.

Node.Caption: MQ201MalbornPostQuestA1: Malborn, it's good to see you.

Cell.Text: I count my blessings every day.

Node.Caption: MQ201MalbornPostQuestA2: At least you're still alive. That's something.

Cell.Text: Don't worry, I'm mad at her, too. And at myself for ever agreeing to get involved in her insane scheme.

Node.Caption: MQ201MalbornPostQuestA3: It's Delphine you should be angry with, not me.

Cell.Text: Trying to stay alive. I think time's running out though. I'm pretty sure the Thalmor know where I am. | Maybe you can help me. You know, by way of making amends for getting me into this mess.
You will? Really? Well, okay, here's the situation.

Node.Caption: MQ201MalbornPostQuestC1: You helped me. I'll do what I can to help you.

Cell.Text: G|Sure, fine. Thanks for nothing. You already got what you needed from me.

Node.Caption: MQ201MalbornPostQuestC2: Sorry, I can't help right now.

Cell.Text: The Thalmor assassin is dead. It's safe to leave Windhelm.

[S] G|That's... great news. I'd... I'd better go. Right now. Before they find me again. This is my chance. | Thank you! Here... I stole a lot from the Thalmor over the years. You may as well have some of it.

[S] S|I was trying to get to Morrowind. The Dunmer don't care much for the Thalmor and I figured I'd be safe there. As safe as anywhere, that is. | But there's a Khajiit hanging around the main gate. I didn't like the way he was looking at me. | I'm sure he's Thalmor. Just waiting for me to leave so he can follow me and kill me in a lonely place.

[S] I was trying to get to Morrowind. The Dunmer don't care much for the Thalmor and I figured I'd be safe there. As safe as anywhere,that is. | But there's a Khajiit hanging around the main gate. I didn't like the way he was looking at me. | I'm sure he's Thalmor. Just waiting for me to leave so he can follow me and kill me in a lonely place.

Node.Caption: MQ201MalbornPostQuestSummary: Tell me about this Thalmor assassin that's hunting you.

Cell.Text: G|You'd be saving my life. Again. I know I probably seemed ungrateful... I've just been so scared. Expecting a knife at my throat any minute.

Node.Caption: MQ201MalbornPostQuestAssassinA1: Don't worry. I'll take care of this assassin for you.

Cell.Text: G|No, you can't ever be too paranoid where the Thalmor is concerned. Look what happened to the Blades. The Blades! | If the damn Blades are no match for the Thalmor, what chance do I have? | Please, just go check it out. You'll be saving my life.

Node.Caption: MQ201MalbornPostQuestAssassinA2: Sounds like you're just being paranoid.

Cell.Text: Move on, friend. I have nothing to sell today.
G|Move on, friend. I have nothing to sell today.
[S] G|Malborn? Ah... very good. I think we understand each other.

Node.Caption: MQ201MalbornAssassinBlockingA1: Malborn has a message for you.

Cell.Text: [S] Ah. You must mean that one over there. He's not one of us. | Thalmor filth, eh? Giving all Khajiit a bad name.

Node.Caption: MQ201MalbornCaravanTopic: I'm looking for a Khajiit... might be a Thalmor spy.
